      <head>Leitmeritz [Cz.: Litomeříce]</head>
      <div>

        <p>Town and episcopal see in Bohemia, approx. 70 km (45 miles) north of Prague. It lies on
          the Elbe River, opposite <ref cRef="entity-007490">Theresienstadt [Terezín]</ref>, and
          during World War II was a subordinate concentration camp of the latter.</p>

        <p>In 1913, <ref cRef="entity-000771">Jeanette Schenker</ref> had dealings with the tax
          authorities in Leitmeritz, presumably because she was born and lived until 1910 in the
          nearby town of <ref cRef="entity-002248">Aussig</ref>.</p>
      </div>
